              <p>I am using K8s to run redash server and worker.<br>
The followings are the summary of the task definition for worker container</p>
<ul>
<li>image: â€˜redash/redash:â€˜9.0.0-beta.b42121â€™</li>
<li>command: â€˜workerâ€™</li>
<li>environment variables
<ul>
<li>REDASH_HOST: â€˜<a href="https://xxxx.com/" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">https://xxxx.com</a>â€™ // url to my redash service</li>
<li>REDASH_REDIS_URL: redisUrl,</li>
<li>REDASH_DATABASE_URL: dbUrl,</li>
<li>REDASH_COOKIE_SECRET: â€˜my-secretâ€™,</li>
<li>QUEUES: â€˜default,queries,scheduled_queries,schemas,emails,periodicâ€™,</li>
<li>WORKERS_COUNT: â€˜4â€™,</li>
<li>REDASH_MAIL_SERVER: â€˜<a href="http://email-smtp.ap-northeast-1.amazonaws.com/" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">email-smtp.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com</a>â€™,</li>
<li>REDASH_MAIL_PORT: â€˜465â€™,</li>
<li>REDASH_MAIL_USERNAME: â€˜XXXXXXXXXâ€™, // access key of SES smtp credential</li>
<li>REDASH_MAIL_PASSWORD: â€˜xxxxxxxxxxxxâ€™, // secret access key of SES smtp credential</li>
<li>REDASH_MAIL_DEFAULT_SENDER: â€˜xxxxx@mydomain.comâ€™,</li>
<li>REDASH_MAIL_USE_TLS: â€˜trueâ€™</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>I have added <code>xxxxx@mydomain.com</code> to AWS SES verified identities.</p>
<p>Could you please tell me how to set up correctly?</p>
<p>Thank you in advance.</p>
